  <h1 id="english">Privacy Policy for Phone Video Organizer</h1>

  <p class="updated">Effective date: Month Day, 2026</p>

  <section>
    <p>
      Phone Video Organizer (the “App”) is an app that helps users review videos stored on their device,
      share selected videos to the YouTube app, and optionally move videos to the device trash.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Information Used by the App</h2>
    <p>
      The App uses permission to access video files on your device in order to display and organize your videos.
    </p>
    <p>The App may use the following information on your device:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Video files stored on your device</li>
      <li>Video file names</li>
      <li>Video creation date or modified date</li>
      <li>Video file size</li>
      <li>Video duration</li>
      <li>Video status in the App, such as pending, skipped, uploaded, or deleted</li>
      <li>App language setting</li>
      <li>Tutorial completion status</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This information is used only to provide the App’s features on your device.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Handling of Video Files</h2>
    <p>
      The App accesses videos on your device so that you can view, play, and organize them.
    </p>
    <p>
      The App does not send your video files to the developer’s server.<br />
      The App does not automatically upload your videos to any external service.
    </p>
    <p>
      Only when you choose “Upload with YouTube app,” the selected video is shared to the YouTube app
      or another app that supports video sharing, based on your action.
    </p>
    <p>
      Uploading, visibility settings, and content management in YouTube are handled by the YouTube app
      and your own actions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Moving Videos to Trash</h2>
    <p>
      The App provides a feature to move selected videos to the device trash.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before moving a video to trash, the App always shows a confirmation screen.<br />
      The App does not delete or move videos to trash without your permission.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Collection and Sharing of Data</h2>
    <p>
      The App does not send video files, personal information, or usage history to the developer’s server.<br />
      The App does not sell or share your personal information with third parties.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you choose to share a video with YouTube or another app, the handling of that video is governed
      by the privacy policy of the selected service or app.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Locally Stored Information</h2>
    <p>The App stores the following information locally on your device:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Video organization status</li>
      <li>Language setting</li>
      <li>Tutorial completion status</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This information is stored on your device to provide the App’s features.<br />
      When you uninstall the App, this information is usually deleted.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      The current version of the App does not contain ads.
    </p>
    <p>
      If ads are added in the future, this Privacy Policy and the Google Play Data safety information
      will be updated accordingly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Accounts</h2>
    <p>
      The App does not provide its own account creation feature.<br />
      The App does not collect or store your YouTube account login information.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
      Email:<br />
      <a href="mailto:ryg4mk@gmail.com">ryg4mk@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.<br />
      If important changes are made, we will notify users in the App or on the distribution page.
    </p>
  </section>

